  "title": "Geological/Instrumentation Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles & Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p>1. Review of all geotechnical design drawings to ensure comply with relevant statutory standard, regulations\nand codes of practices.</p><p>2. Project coordination including submission to local authorities and liaison during the construction stage.</p><p>3. Co-ordinate with authorities, client and consultants</p><p>4. Evaluate subcontractor’s risk assessment, safe work procedures and method statements</p><p>5. Plan and execute geotechnical and instrumentation installation and monitoring works</p><p>6. Prepare instrumentation reports</p><p>7. Site evaluation of soil, rock, fault distribution and geological studies on and below the site to determine\ntheir engineering properties</p><p>8. Liaise and coordinate with instrumentation contractor for installation and monitoring issues</p><p>9. Update instrumentation drawings</p><p>10. Responsible for attendance to daily site coordination meeting and provide detail coordination with subcontractors.</p><p><strong>Requirements and relevant experience are as below:</strong></p><p>1. Bachelor’s / Master’s Degree of Civil Engineering or close discipline;</p><p>2. Minimum 5 years of experience in Geotechnical Engineering especially for LTA Project</p><p>3. Be well-aware of Geotechnical Design, Instrumentation & Monitoring process</p><p>4. Be well-aware of Underground Structure/Construction Sequences and related civil design works.</p><p>5. Be well-aware of Eurocode, LTA CDC, and relevant design specification/standards</p><p>* Candidates who has experience as Geotechnical engineer in D&B contractor side would be an advantage.</p><p>* Interested applicants are required to submit their detailed CV and state their current and expected\nsalary.</p>",
